column5: Have got the chance to get out fishing with my girlfriend and her parents lately up in the Kawarthas. Fishing wasn't to bad,  I managed to get a 5 pound 19 inch Largie throwing a spinner bait along a matt of grass.      Wasn't quite big enough to make it on the board for Team 7 but it's my personal best. Girlfriends dad was impressed and has decided to get it mounted  We tried to get out last weekend again and got rear ended by another vehicle on the way The prop broke and had to wait for the insurance company so the boat had to go back. We were all packed so we decided to still go do a little shore fishing anyways. Got a couple small bass and ended up catching a small musky and loosing two others    but was still ended up being a good day. Heres the Musky.
good on ya for still getting out (after the accident) and nice fish too.
Nice fish, to bad about the boat...
Beauty bass and great job on the muskie from shore! Sorry to hear about the boat, hopefully it'll be fixed soon. Thanks for the report!
Nice bucket mouth!!!Congrats on your PB.  Sucks about the accident. Hopefully you get your boat up and running soon! Thanks for sharing.
SEXY BUCKET!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  Gotta love kawarthas man
That's a great bass.  Nice little ski too, that was a bonus.  Sorry to hear about the accident and the boat.  Hope its fixed and up and running soon.  Joey
